                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18231203-51-victim558 t18231203-51-viclabel276"></join> to the 
               <persName id="t18231203-51-person560">
                  Honourable 
                  S. Berkeley
               <interp inst="t18231203-51-person560" type="surname" value="S. Berkeley"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18231203-51-person560" type="given" value="Honourable"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18231203-51-person560" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , of <placeName id="t18231203-51-crimeloc277">Cranford Bridge</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18231203-51-crimeloc277" type="placeName" value="Cranford Bridge"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18231203-51-crimeloc277" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18231203-51-off274 t18231203-51-crimeloc277"></join>. On the 19th of November, at seven o'clock in the evening, I left the property stated in the indictment in my room over the stable. The prisoner lived in the Countess's service nine months ago. I missed this property at nine o'clock, and between one and two in the morning Webb brought the prisoner to me with them. He gave me 13 s. 6 d., and said, "Here is your money, Daniel, which I had out of your pocket."</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18231203-51-person561">
                  THOMAS 
                  WEBB
               <interp inst="t18231203-51-person561" type="surname" value="WEBB"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18231203-51-person561" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18231203-51-person561" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live at Cranford. I heard of this robbery; went in search of the thief, and overtook the prisoner at the Green Man, public-house, seven miles off, at eleven o'clock, and found the waistcoat on his back. He had two pair of breeches, a handkerchief, and a pair of boots on. I took him to Whitton. He said, "Here is your money - I have spent one shilling."</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18231203-51-verdict278" type="verdictDescription">
